
* Servers are general purpose computing machines, the same as a single-user machine
  * Treating a particular server as the authoritative "source of truth" is useful when it comes to input data, because it serves a synchronizing function
  * Carrying out demanding computations on a centralized server can also be useful, because it reduces redundancy
* Development needs to take the production environment's resource constraints into account, but it should not create unnecessary tight coupling with that environment
